radiographic_examinations.findings: In segment VIII of the liver, there is a 1.6 x 1.3 cm hypodense lesion likely representing a cyst. Two smaller 4-mm hypodensities are also in the liver. The appendix is mildly dilated measuring up to 8 mm in diameter with very early wall hyperemia distally. No air is seen within the appendix. Minimal bibasilar dependent atelectasis. No pleural or pericardial effusion is seen. The spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands and kidneys are unremarkable. No upper abdominal free fluid or free air is seen. The prostate is normal in size. No pelvic free fluid or free air is seen.
